yoga_list.name: Gajakesari Yoga
yoga_list.description: Someone with Gaja Kesari Yoga is considered to be really lucky. This yoga is as a result of the Moon and Jupiter coming together by being in the 1st, 4th, 7th, or 10th Kendra from each other.  It is believed that a person born with this yoga in their horoscope will be blessed with the intellect of an elephant and the grandeur of a lion. For one to truly benefit from the Gajakesari yoga, the aspect and conjunction must be at the most optimum position. This is why we donâ€™t see the true positive effect of the Gaja Kesari Yoga in the lives of all those who are supposedly born with this yoga in their horoscope.In this chart Jupiter is in kendras from Moon.

yoga_list.name: Kahal Yoga
yoga_list.description: Kahala yoga occurs when the Lords of the 4th and 9th houses are in mutual Kendras and there exists a strong Lord of the Lagna. An individual with Kahala yoga may have contradictory  characteristics. One moment they are the brightest minds in the room, the next instant they may make the silliest of mistakes of take an irresponsible decision. Ups and downs in life is typical of someone with Kahala yoga. In this chart 4th Lord and 10th Lord are in conjunction.

yoga_list.name: Musala Yoga
yoga_list.description: When all the planets and the Lagna are in the Fixed signs like Taurus, Leo, Scorpio and Aquarius, a Musala yoga is the end result. Those with this yoga tend to be very straight forward about their ethos and principles in life. Administrative jobs are an excellent career choice for such people. Fame and prestigious achievements are likely to follow such people as a reward for their diligence. However such individuals don't roll well with change. Flexibility is definitely not their forte.

yoga_list.name: Raja Yoga
yoga_list.description: A typical Raja Yoga happens when two or more than two planets (out of which atleast one should be the lord of 'Kendra' & the other should be the lord of 'Trikon') is in a relationship with each other. This relationship can be a combination, bidirectional vision or exchange of zodiacs. A person with a Raja Yoga enjoys social status and fame.  Recognition and laurels will follow them for their efforts on various matters. In this chart there is relationship between Moon and Mars planets.

yoga_list.name: Sasa Yoga
yoga_list.description: Sasa Yoga, being one of the five of Panchmaha Purusha Yoga is a really auspicious yoga. When Saturn is in its own sign (Capricorn or Aquarius) or in its exaltation sign (Libra) and occupies Kendra house either from Ascendant or from Moon, a Sasa yoga is the result. The native of Sasa yoga loves travelling and is very appreciative of beauty and nature. They are noble and humble in all their endeavours. They are known to do well in politics. In this chart Saturn is in its own sign.

yoga_list.name: Anafa Yoga
yoga_list.description: Anafa Yoga is as a result of a benefic planet (except Sun, Rahu and Ketu) in the twelfth house from Moon. The native of Anafa yoga enjoys good health. They will be able to get people on their side with their charm and wit. They will be a master in communication and  may also be interest in humanitarian causes and charitable acts. In this chart planet Mars is in the 12th house from Moon.

yoga_list.name: Veshi Yoga
yoga_list.description: Veshi yoga is formed when the planets Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter or Saturn is in the second house from Sun. Person born in this yoga do not discriminate between people. They are deeply religious and are usually happy go lucky people.In this chart planets Venus and Saturn are in the 2nd house from Sun.

yoga_list.name: Vaasi Yoga
yoga_list.description: Vashi yoga is found in a birth chart when any planet except Rahu, Ketu and Moon is placed in the twelfth house from the Sun. Wealth, luxury and joy are seen to follow those with this yoga. Those with Vaasi yoga have a likeable personality and are talented, intelligent, systematic and diligent in anything that they undertake. They are honest and true to their words at all times. In this chart planet Mercury is in the 12th house from Sun.

yoga_list.name: Ubhayachari Yoga
yoga_list.description: Ubhayachari yoga is seen in a person's birth chart when there are any planets except Rahu, Ketu and Moon in the second house and twelfth house from the Sun. The natives of this yoga enjoy good health and will be surrounded by friends wherever they go. In this chart planets Mercury, Venus and Saturn are on either side of sun.
